Key Match Events: Jan Frylinck scored a 48-ball 45 for Namibia
Ruben Trumpelmann took three wickets in his first two overs
David Wiese became the fourth player in men's T20Is to bat and bowl in a Super Over
Post-Match Reflections: Oman captain Bilal Khan was left ruing the chances they put down
Namibia captain David Wiese praised his team's composed performance in the Super Over
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the third time a men's T20 World Cup game went to the Super Over and the first since 2012
Namibia bowled 44 deliveries without conceding a boundary, allowing Oman just 29 runs in this period
Others: Mehran Khan bowled tight lines and lengths to restrict Namibia's chase
Oman's Zeeshan Maqsood tried to get his team back on track with a flurry of boundaries
